    "m_Type": "UnityEditor.ShaderGraph.StickyNoteData",
    "m_ObjectId": "86e8f55d077f433297305d20f078c49c",
    "m_Title": "DarkColour",
    "m_Content": "This upper half has to do with the lower \"layer\" of the shader, that being the darker colour under the explosion that gives it added depth and simulates smoke clouds. The two are added together at the end, with the lighter layer \"FireColour\" being on top as the brighter layer.",
